<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>During which phase of the business cycle would expansionary fiscal policy be most appropriate?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">When there is an inflationary gap</option>
            <option letter="b">When there is a recessionary gap</option>
            <option letter="c">When the economy is at full employment</option>
            <option letter="d">When there is stagflation</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Expansionary fiscal policy (increased government spending or tax cuts) is most appropriate during a recessionary gap when actual GDP is below potential GDP. This policy helps stimulate aggregate demand to close the gap and bring the economy back to full employment.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
